The paper deals with the problem of detecting communities in social networks, which falls under the subfield of network science. The paper proposes a novel algorithm for detecting communities with significant overlaps, which involves merging partial information from ego networks of vertices. This algorithmic approach is likely to be of interest to researchers in the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SOC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed algorithm against existing benchmarks, which falls under the sub-category of performance evaluation (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the need for new algorithms to handle multiple memberships of vertices in social networks, which is relevant to the sub-category of social informatics (cs.SD).
